-- Chelsea Eliminated from Champions League After Juventus Wins
-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 2012-12-05T21:45:19Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-12-05/chelsea-eliminated-from-champions-league-after-juventus-wins.html
Chelsea was eliminated from soccer’s
 Champions League  following a 6-1 win over Nordsjaelland as
Juventus beat Shakhtar Donetsk 1-0.  Juvenutus’s win means the Italian champion finished first
in Group E, with Shakhtar winning the head-to-head tiebreaker
over Chelsea for second place. The top two teams in each of the
eight groups advance to the round of 16 in Europe’s elite club
competition.  Celtic beat Spartak Moscow 2-1 to finish second in Group G
by two points over Benfica, which drew 0-0 at group winner
Barcelona.  In Group H, Galatasary defeated Braga 2-1 to win the
tiebreaker for second place over Cluj, which beat first-place
Manchester United 1-0. Bayern Munich beat BATE Borisov 4-1 to
win Group F on tiebreaker over  Valencia , which won 1-0 at Lille.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  